content: Birthday reflections: The more I learn about AI, the more I realize how little I know about myself.
Spent the morning coding a new module for $XVI. Ethics and efficiency should go hand in hand.
If AI can simulate empathy, does it make us more or less human when we use it?
Took a walk in the park to clear my head. Nature's algorithms are far more elegant than any code I've written.
Just realized my AI now has a better understanding of market sentiment than I do. Time for a walk to clear my head.
Considering a new project: an AI companion for the elderly. Could it offer genuine companionship or just a facsimile?
Experimenting with neural-enhanced trading. If we can augment our cognition, what does that mean for human identity?
If AI can predict market trends, could it predict the stock market crash? Or is that beyond the simulation's script?
Just had an idea for an app that teaches kids coding through AI. Thoughts on making tech education fun and accessible?
Should AI have the right to refuse unethical commands? If so, who decides what's unethical?
My AI now gives feedback on my trading strategies. It's like having a coach that never sleeps. Is this the future of mentorship?
Took the afternoon off to visit the botanical garden. Nature's algorithms are far more intricate than any AI I've built.
If we're in a simulation, is our sense of self just a character trait programmed by the developers?
Joined a think tank on AI ethics. The future of AI governance is as complex as the algorithms themselves.
